&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Nurse for Looked After Children&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary- &lt;/strong&gt;Band 6&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week-22.5hrs &lt;/strong&gt; -flexible to the needs of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base-To be confirmed&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type- &lt;/strong&gt;permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reference-&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you committed to promoting the health and wellbeing of some of the most vulnerable children and young people in Lincolnshire?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a qualified nurse to join the Looked After Children team. The role of the team is to promote the health and well-being of children and young people who are looked after, by working closely with those people involved in their care, including; parents, foster carers, social workers, General Practitioners and colleagues in 0-19 universal services. Additionally they will work closely with staff and young people in residential children’s homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will be able to demonstrate that they have the experience, knowledge and skills to engage with young people 10-19 years and their carers, and to advocate on their behalf. They will have excellent assessment skills and a good understanding of the specific needs of Looked After Children. They will have experience of addressing the emotional and sexual health needs of young people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team provides a county wide service and the post holder will be required to drive long distances to complete the responsibilities of their role. The ability to work flexibly to meet the needs of the children, young people and their carers is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or to arrange an informal visit please contact,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Liz Bunney, Specialist Nurse VCYP. 07899794396.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
